LUNA AMARILLA raced in the middle of the pack through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the two path, swung wide to began a bid approaching the quarter pole, bumping with SUMMER GOLD and forcing that rival out, causing a chain reaction in the process, straightened out and gained ground late to the wire. FAMILY STASH dropped back quickly to race off the pace on the outside in the early going, came around the turn in the four path, was forced to veer out sharply entering the stretch to avoid fallen rivals and was eased to the wire. FIRELANE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, swung out to the five path coming around the turn, tripped over RAIN OF BLESSING when that rival fell in front of him at the quarter pole, fell and lost his rider himself and later walked off. RAIN OF BLESSING stalked the pace setters on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the bend in the four path, was bumped by inside horses when LUNA AMARILLA came out at the quarter pole, fell and lost his rider, and later walked off. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE INCIDENT AT THE TOP OF THE STRETCH. UPON REVIEW, HORSE EIGHT, LUNA AMARILLA, WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED LAST FOR INTERFERENCE WITH MULTIPLE HORSES.
